      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how exhausting that feeling of being a \"hollow shell\" can be, and it makes sense why you feel disconnected from the people around you. When the internal experience feels so detached, the effort to connect externally can feel pointless or even draining. It's a heavy burden to carry when you feel like you're performing a role rather than living it.\n\nIt sounds like you're in a really tough spot right now, and that sense of fakeness is incredibly isolating. While I can't change how you feel, I'm here to listen if you want to talk about what's going on or just vent. Sometimes, just having a space to express that exhaustion without judgment can help lighten the load, even if the feeling itself doesn't disappear immediately.",
